summary: An FBI communication from Sacramento to Miami regarding the obstruction of justice case against Alfredo Rodriguez. It details the acquisition of California driver's license photographs for two individuals (names redacted) as part of the investigation.

persons.name: Alfredo Rodriguez
persons.context: Named in the case title for obstruction of justice. The document is part of an investigation into him.

persons.name: SA PB-2
persons.context: The FBI agent in Miami to whom the communication is addressed.

persons.name: M:kml
persons.context: The individual who drafted the FBI communication.

connections.description: SA PB-2 is the receiving agent for investigative materials related to the obstruction of justice case against Rodriguez.

events.title: Acquisition of DMV Records
events.description: The records section of the California Department of Motor Vehicles provided driver's license photographs for two individuals to the FBI.

keyFacts: The document is part of FBI case 72-MM-113327, targeting Alfredo Rodriguez for obstruction of justice.
On June 4, 2010, the FBI obtained California driver's license photographs for two individuals (names redacted in the summary) from the DMV.
The communication is an internal FBI routing of evidence (photographs and information sheets) from Sacramento to the Miami field office.
